claim.claim-text:
1. A semiconductor memory device comprising: 
a plurality of memory cells arranged in rows and columns; 
a plurality of bit lines, arranged corresponding to the columns of the memory cells, each having the memory cells on a corresponding column connected; 
a plurality of word lines, arranged corresponding to the rows of the memory cells, each having the memory cells on a corresponding row connected; 
a plurality of first sense amplifiers each disposed corresponding to a set of a predetermined number of bit lines, for sensing and amplifying data of a memory cell on a corresponding column when activated; 
a plurality of first transfer gates disposed corresponding to the respective bit lines, each for connecting a corresponding bit line and a corresponding first sense amplifier when made conductive; and 
connection control circuitry for selectively making said plurality of first transfer gates conductive in response to an operation mode instruction signal, said connection control circuitry making the transfer gates disposed for a first pair of bit lines out of said predetermined number of bit lines conductive in each set in a first operation mode, and making the transfer gates disposed for a second pair of bit lines different from the first pair of bit lines out of said predetermined number of bit lines conductive in each set in a second operation mode.
